  "title": "What has this got to do with Holochain?",
  "story": [
    {
      "type": "markdown",
      "id": "0b09368e4a8923fb",
      "text": "##Three reasons: philosophy, technology and metaphor.\n\n 1. PHILOSOPHY: LiquidWiki embodies a high-level version of how agent-centric data models support structured interchange between autonomous agents: each writer has their own data integrity, but at the same time all content is open to discovery, to re-use, to re-purposing. There is no 'canonical' version of the truth, but at the same time the social nature of the operational space tends towards co-creation.\n\n 2. TECHNOLOGY: As presently coded, Federated Wiki's provenance chain is not encrypted and thus insecure. Holo's hashchain approach resolves this issue in an integrated way. This can enable a variety of uses where guarantees of authenticity of history are fundamental - Liquid Democracy is one example.\n\n3. METAPHOR: To work in LiquidWiki is to act as a decentralised but socially connected agent - freely accessing the data stores of other agents on the network, but without changing their state."
